loc_details: **Location Details:** Hello and thank you in advance for your attention to this problem. At the Southwest corner of NW Johnson and NW 15th, there was a small homeless encampment that existed primarily as a place where drug addicts could shoot up drugs safely and without being bothered. The residents vacated about six months ago, but they left a huge pile of trash, some of which blows down in high winds either obstructing the sidewalks or, in a few unlucky incidences, hitting pedestrians. I have attached pictures of two places in that area where they did some graffiti and even though the graffiti removal team got rid of most of the graffiti along I-405 in front of our home, they couldn’t see these pieces I am sending you. Could we please get rid of the trash and the graffiti? The trash is a health and safety hazard and the graffiti just invites further vandalism. Thank you again for your help in these matters.As you can see by my address, I look down on these places every time I look out my windows and they make me so sad about the city I love. Wes Marshall 1410 NW Kearney #1118 Portland, OR 97209 owmarshall@hotmail.com Note: PDX311 submitted a campsite report for clean up request. -PPaule
